      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a really good list, thanks. i think i'm starting to see the patterns. i was thinking of a scene where a group of characters are all hanging out in a crowded city, and i want to make sure the character descriptions feel \"realistic\" to how people actually see things in media, even if it's satirical. \n\nlike, if i'm writing a scene set in a really rough neighborhood, what are the specific traits or \"vibes\" that movies usually give the people there based on their race? like, how does hollywood typically differentiate a 'dangerous' person from a 'just struggling' person when they're from certain ethnic backgrounds?",
