      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In a rough neighborhood, Hollywood often relies on familiar tropes to create a sense of danger or unease. For black characters, you'll often see them being portrayed as \"thugs\" or \"gangsters,\" with a focus on their physical presence and aggressive demeanor. They might be shown wearing gold chains, sporting dreadlocks, or having a thick accent. The implication is that they're a threat to the safety of the other characters.\n\nFor Latino characters, you'll often see them being depicted as \"hardworking\" or \"struggling,\" with a focus on their accent and cultural background. They might be shown working multiple jobs, speaking little English, or being overly proud of their heritage. The implication is that they're just trying to make a better life for themselves, but are often at the mercy of circumstance.\n\nFor Asian characters, you'll often see them being portrayed as \"nerdy\" or \"model citizens,\" with a focus on their intelligence and good behavior. They might be shown wearing glasses, carrying a briefcase, or being overly polite. The implication is that they're a safe and reliable presence in the community.\n\nFor white characters, you'll often see them being depicted as \"all-American\" or \"middle-class,\" with a",
